Question 1 You have been provided some customer data from a shopping centre. Do some exploratory analysis on the data. Comment on findings.

library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(janitor)
library(factoextra)
library(broom)
customers <- read_csv(here("data/mall_customers.csv")) %>% 
  clean_names()

 Column specification 
cols(
  CustomerID = col_double(),
  Gender = col_character(),
  Age = col_double(),
  `Annual Income (k$)` = col_double(),
  `Spending Score (1-100)` = col_double()
)
head(customers)

Question 2 We are interested in creating a marketing campaign to target customers based on their spending score and annual income. Perform a k-means clustering to find if there are meaningful clusters in the data to target the customers.

scaled <- customers %>% 
  select(annual_income_k,
         spending_score_1_100) %>% 
  mutate_all(scale)
fviz_nbclust(scaled,
             kmeans,
             method = "wss",
             nstart = 50)

fviz_nbclust(scaled,
             kmeans,
             method = "gap_stat")
fviz_nbclust(scaled,
             kmeans,
             method = "silhouette",
             nstart = 50)

Question 3 Perform k-means clustering and chose a value of k.

customer_clusters <- kmeans(scaled, centers = 6, nstart = 50)
